author: The Current
description: Jill Riley from The Current’s Morning Show had an impromptu visit by the legendary Jimmy Jam and author Andrea Swensson, where they discussed the closing of Palmer’s Bar, reconnecting with Cornbread Harris, and much more.
title: Music legend Jimmy Jam talks about the closing night of Minneapolis' beloved Palmer's Bar. #jimmyjam

author: The Current
description:
Watch Yam Haus’ acoustic performance of “One Bullet Left”
Support The Current: https://support.mpr.org/youtube or hit the Thanks button

Just before playing a full set at The Current’s Happy Hour event on August 7, 2025, at Milk & Honey Cider in the central Minnesota town of St. Joseph, Yam Haus performed this impromptu, acoustic version of their song, “One Bullet Left.” Watch their performance above.

Musicians
Lars Pruitt – vocals, guitar
Zach Beinlich – backing vocals
Jake Felstow – percussion, backing vocals

author: The Current
description: Mike Kota’s captivating voice and enriching musical style has earned her spots opening for superstars like Hozier, or performing in front of thousands at the Minnesota Yacht Club Festival. The Minneapolis-based artist’s new breakup single “Boy” can be heard on The Local Show. Check out Mike Kota’s full EP 'Through Fire,' out now. Hit Play!
